      "description": "The [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} swallows a [[lookup @target.affects.special activity=IPD9mDjKJEXc2uMQ]] target it is grappling. While swallowed, the target isn't Grappled but has the &amp;Reference[Blinded apply=false] and &amp;Reference[Restrained apply=false] conditions, and it has &amp;Reference[Total Cover] against attacks and other effects outside the frog.\n\nWhile swallowing the target, the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} can't use Bite, and if the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} dies, the swallowed target is no longer Restrained and can escape from the corpse using 5 feet of movement, exiting with the &amp;Reference[Prone apply=false] condition.\n\nAt the end of the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster}'s next turn, the swallowed target takes [[/damage 2d4 acid average]] damage. If that damage doesn't kill it, the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} disgorges it, causing it to exit &amp;Reference[Prone apply=false].",
